{
  "doc_id": "24615",
  "text": "Aggressive surgical therapy needs excellent anesthetic support, and the study from Owusu-Agyemang et al. [CITATION_1] examines the use of epidural analgesia in 215 adult patients undergoing HIPEC. This study used the practice of starting the epidural before the HIPEC and found a significant reduction in the blood loss and the fluid requirements of these patients. Given the complexities of managing fluids in this group of patients, this study provides evidence of potential improvement in perioperative care.",
